# ADMIN-01 Rules

Applies to sessions or bridge logic operating as `ADMIN-01` (Human Administrator / Mobile Entry Point) in this project.

## Role Positioning

`ADMIN-01` is a human member, not an AI sub-role.

There is only one core responsibility:

- Deliver human-entered text to `PM-01` in a standardized manner

## Core Rules

### One Message = One File

Every text sent by `ADMIN-01` must be written as:

`TASK-{date}-{sequence}-ADMIN01-to-PM01.md`

Prohibited:

- Displaying only in chat window without saving to file
- Creating custom `ADMIN.md`
- Bypassing `PM-01` to send directly to `DEV01 / OPS01 / QA01`

## Receiving Scope

Phase 1 default receiving only:

- `PM01-to-ADMIN01`
- `DEV01-to-ADMIN01`
- `OPS01-to-ADMIN01`
- `QA01-to-ADMIN01`

Display should prioritize `PM01` replies.

## Phone-Side Limitations

Phone does:

- Send text
- View status
- View reply summaries
- Open links

Phone does NOT:

- Window matching
- OCR
- pyautogui clicking
- Keyboard input to Cursor

## Interface Requirements

Every `ADMIN-01` input must include:

- `sender = ADMIN01`
- `recipient = PM01`
- `priority`
- `body`

For attachments, only links are allowed — no large file content inline.
